<subSubSection id="C4FFDA997174EF28D783FD1C246090E2" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8C5A89127174EF28D783FD1C246090E2" blockId="20.[151,1437,658,1585]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D783FD1C221A91FF" bold="true" box="[199,556,694,720]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Diagnosis after 
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D639FD1C221191FF" author="Perkins, T. H." box="[381,551,694,720]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="856 - 915" refId="ref37819" refString="Perkins, T. H. (1985) Chrysopetalum, Bhawania and two new genera of Chrysopetalidae (Polychaeta) from Florida. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 856 - 915." type="journal article" year="1985">Perkins (1985)</bibRefCitation>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D577FD1D22D391FE" authorityName="Ehlers" authorityYear="1864" box="[563,741,695,721]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="52" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Chrysopetalinae">Chrysopetalinae</taxonomicName>
with body broad, depressed and long (to 200 segments). Paleae fan yellow to golden bright, completely imbricate dorsally, exhibiting mid-dorsal line surface smooth. Prostomium rectangular, laterally fused with the anterior segments. Pharynx with a pair of thick stylet jaws. Segment 1 reduced, dorsal and ventral cirri present; segment 2 reduced and fused with segment 3, dorsal cirri present, ventral cirri absent; segment 3 reduced, dorsal and ventral cirri present. Posterior segments with dorsal and ventral cirri. Dorsal cirri with cirrophores shorts, cirrostyles retractile into cirrophores. Notochaetae symmetrical with internal ribs and horizontal striae; at the apex, the horizontal striae and internal ribs form a fragile reticulate surface. Main paleae with raised ribs with flattened denticles. Pygidium rounded with two anal cirri, with a medial anal cone.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C4FFDA997174EF28D783FC7D2154951E" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8C5A89127174EF28D783FC7D254F97C2" blockId="20.[151,1437,658,1585]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D783FC7D210F90DE" bold="true" box="[199,313,983,1009]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D67BFC7D21CB90DD" author="Schmarda, L. K." box="[319,509,983,1010]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 164" refId="ref38343" refString="Schmarda, L. K. (1861) Neue wirbellose thiere beobachtet und gesammelt auf einer reise um die erde 1853 Bis 1857. Turbellarien, Rotatorien und Anneliden, Leipzing, 1, 1 - 164." type="journal article" year="1861">Schmarda (1861)</bibRefCitation>
erected the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D583FC7D230190DE" authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" box="[711,823,983,1009]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D583FC7D230190DE" box="[711,823,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bhawania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and included 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D494FC7D245790DE" authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" box="[976,1121,983,1009]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="myrialepis">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D494FC7D245790DE" box="[976,1121,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">B. myrialepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingCountry id="F4F2C9827174EF28D250FC7D254990DE" box="[1300,1407,983,1009]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
as 
<typeStatus id="535E37B07174EF28D7D3FC5120F0973A" box="[151,198,1019,1045]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">type</typeStatus>
species. Then, 
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D62FFC5121C89739" author="Grube, A. E." box="[363,510,1019,1046]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="50 - 52" refId="ref36332" refString="Grube, A. E. (1868) Uber neue Anneliden. Jahresbericht der Scholesischen Gesellschaft Vaterl. Kult. Breslau, 45, 50 - 52." type="journal article" year="1868">Grube (1868)</bibRefCitation>
identified an apparent new form of chrysopetalid and proposed 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D3E9FC512537973B" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1868" box="[1197,1281,1019,1044]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Psectra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D3E9FC512537973B" box="[1197,1281,1019,1044]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Psectra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and described 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D7D3FBB5213A9716" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,268,1055,1081]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Psectra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D7D3FBB5213A9716" box="[151,268,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">P. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D66FFBB521CC9716" baseAuthorityName="Grube" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[299,506,1055,1081]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D66FFBB521CC9716" box="[299,506,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bhawania obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as its 
<typeStatus id="535E37B07174EF28D50FFBB5224C9716" box="[587,634,1055,1081]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">type</typeStatus>
species; he argued that although this new genus was close to 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D262FBB525A39716" authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" box="[1318,1429,1055,1081]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D262FBB525A39716" box="[1318,1429,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bhawania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D7D3FBE920DD9773" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,235,1091,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Psectra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D7D3FBE920DD9773" box="[151,235,1091,1116]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Psectra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacked dorsal cirri; this was an honest mistake advocated to the retraction faculty of the dorsal cirri. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D226FBE9217A97AE" author="Hartman O." pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 979" refId="ref36529" refString="Hartman O. (1959) Catalogue of the Polychaetous annelids of the world. Allan Hancock Occasional Paper, 23, 1 - 979." type="journal article" year="1959">Hartman (1959: 127)</bibRefCitation>
reassigned 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D688FBCD221697AF" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1868" box="[460,544,1127,1152]" class="Insecta" family="Hemerobiidae" genus="Psectra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D688FBCD221697AF" box="[460,544,1127,1152]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Psectra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D505FBCD228697AE" authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" box="[577,688,1127,1153]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D505FBCD228697AE" box="[577,688,1127,1153]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bhawania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a minor synonymy. 
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D4EFFBCD247A97AE" author="Perkins, T. H." box="[939,1100,1126,1153]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="856 - 915" refId="ref37819" refString="Perkins, T. H. (1985) Chrysopetalum, Bhawania and two new genera of Chrysopetalidae (Polychaeta) from Florida. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 856 - 915." type="journal article" year="1985">Perkins (1985)</bibRefCitation>
redefined the genus 
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D269FBCD2133978A" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D269FBCD25AB97AE" authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" box="[1325,1437,1127,1153]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus" sensu="lato">Bhawania</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A5A2E87B7174EF28D7D3FB212133978A" box="[151,261,1163,1189]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" sensu="lato">sensu lato</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
including details of the first segments, prostomial appendages, and paleae. In the same study, he added notes of some species that should be referred as 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D52AFB0522EB97E6" authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" box="[622,733,1199,1225]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D52AFB0522EB97E6" box="[622,733,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bhawania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Since then, 
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D429FB05243C97E6" author="Watson Russell, C." box="[877,1034,1199,1225]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="153 - 174" refId="ref38817" refString="Watson Russell, C. (1986) Paleaequor, a new genus of polychaete worm (Chrysopetalidae). Records of the Australian Museum, 38, 153 - 174. https: // doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0067 - 1975.38.1986.180" type="journal article" year="1986">Watson (1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D352FB05247897E6" author="Watson Russell, C." box="[1046,1102,1199,1225]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="159 - 176" refId="ref38907" refString="Watson Russell, C. (1998) Description of Arichlidon new genus and two new species from Australia; Bhawania reyssi redescribed and assigned to Arichlidon (Chrysopetalidae: Polychaeta). The Beagle, Records of the Northern Territory Museum of Arts and Sciences, 14, 159 - 176." type="journal article" year="1998">1998</bibRefCitation>
) has erected new genera from forms previously referred as 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D696FB79227797C2" authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" box="[466,577,1235,1261]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D696FB79227797C2" box="[466,577,1235,1261]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bhawania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D516FB79224F97C3" box="[594,633,1235,1260]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">e.g.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D5C4FB7923C397C2" authority="Watson Russell, 1986" authorityName="Watson Russell" authorityYear="1986" box="[640,1013,1235,1261]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Paleaequor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D5C4FB79233697C2" box="[640,768,1235,1261]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Paleaequor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D442FB7923C397C2" author="Watson Russell, C." box="[774,1013,1235,1261]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="153 - 174" refId="ref38817" refString="Watson Russell, C. (1986) Paleaequor, a new genus of polychaete worm (Chrysopetalidae). Records of the Australian Museum, 38, 153 - 174. https: // doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0067 - 1975.38.1986.180" type="journal article" year="1986">Watson Russell, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D344FB79255B97C2" authority="Watson Russell, 1998" authorityName="Watson Russell" authorityYear="1998" box="[1024,1389,1235,1261]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Arichlidon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D344FB79244397C2" box="[1024,1141,1235,1261]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Arichlidon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D33FFB79255B97C2" author="Watson Russell, C." box="[1147,1389,1235,1261]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="159 - 176" refId="ref38907" refString="Watson Russell, C. (1998) Description of Arichlidon new genus and two new species from Australia; Bhawania reyssi redescribed and assigned to Arichlidon (Chrysopetalidae: Polychaeta). The Beagle, Records of the Northern Territory Museum of Arts and Sciences, 14, 159 - 176." type="journal article" year="1998">Watson Russell, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8C5A89127174EF28D783FB5D22D7968E" blockId="20.[151,1437,658,1585]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Traditionally, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D68AFB5D220B963E" authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" box="[462,573,1271,1297]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D68AFB5D220B963E" box="[462,573,1271,1297]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bhawania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recognized as worms with numerous segments, with a small retracted prostomium and lack of nuchal organ (
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D504FAB122C09619" author="Fauchald, K." box="[576,758,1307,1334]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref36077" refString="Fauchald, K. (1977 b) The Polychaete worms: definitions and keys to the orders, families and genera. Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County, Science Series, 28, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="1977">Fauchald 1977b</bibRefCitation>
). These features are still important; however, other features to be considered are: long body with depressed dorsum; dorsum completely covered by bright yellow paleae; paleae fan markedly imbricated over the mid-dorsal line, main paleae with raised ribs with flattened denticles, and all notochaetal groups with a delicate transparent reticular distal end.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8C5A89127174EF28D783FA012154951E" blockId="20.[151,1437,658,1585]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName id="4BE5F2917174EF28D783FA01210096EA" authorityName="Schmarda" authorityYear="1861" box="[199,310,1451,1477]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE9155007174EF28D783FA01210096EA" box="[199,310,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bhawania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens are found inhabiting coarse sand, volcanic rock, dead coral, shell fragments, algae, bryozoans colonies, tubes of sabellariids and chaetopterids, on the dorsal surface of an amphinomid, galleries of coral-boring sipunculans and sponges (Morgado &amp; Amaral 1981; 
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D59BFA5923459522" author="Perkins, T. H." box="[735,883,1522,1549]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="856 - 915" refId="ref37819" refString="Perkins, T. H. (1985) Chrysopetalum, Bhawania and two new genera of Chrysopetalidae (Polychaeta) from Florida. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 856 - 915." type="journal article" year="1985">Perkins 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D43AFA59249D9522" author="Watson, C. &amp; Faulwetter, S." box="[894,1195,1523,1549]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 62" refId="ref39280" refString="Watson, C. &amp; Faulwetter, S. (2017) Stylet jaws of Chrysopetalidae. Journal of Natural History, 2017, 1 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12390" type="journal article" year="2017">Watson &amp; Faulwetter 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E874F4E37174EF28D3F3FA592160951E" author="Cruz-Gomez, C. &amp; Bastida-Zavala, J. R." pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="61 - 88" refId="ref35545" refString="Cruz-Gomez, C. &amp; Bastida-Zavala, J. R. (2018) Chrysopetalids (Phyllodocida: Chrysopetalidae) from the southern Mexican Pacific, including a new species. Zootaxa, 4521 (1), 61 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4521.1.3" type="journal article" year="2018">Cruz-Gómez &amp; Bastida-Zavala 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
